content:
Embed a Custom Lightning Web Component, a FlexCard, or an OmniScript in a FlexCard

Create and activate a FlexCard, a custom LWC component, or an LWC OmniScript to generate a Lightning web component to embed in your FlexCard state. 

In the FlexCard designer, open a FlexCard and drag a Custom LWC element from the Build panel into the FlexCard.

(Optional) Enter an element name. For Custom LWC Name, select the custom LWC to embed.

Set the componentâ€™s attributes. Click +Add and enter a name, such as thumbnaillimit. Select a merge field, supported context variable, or text for Value.

(Optional) To add conditions for displaying the element, see Add Conditions to a FlexCard Element.
(Optional) To style your element, click Style. See Style FlexCard Elements.

Preview your FlexCard. See Preview a FlexCard.

Custom LWC element properties are configurable in the Property Panel when you select a Custom LWC element in the FlexCard Designer.

SEE ALSO
FlexCards Custom LWC Properties
title: Embedding Custom Components in OmniStudio FlexCards
